{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"eunomia-bpf","page":{"layout":"document","title":"github template","description":"eunomia-template：使用 GitHub Actions 编译 eBPF 程序，并将生成的 package.json 发布为 Release 资产。历史上的 ebpm-template 仓库现在会重定向到这里。","descriptionIsExcerpt":true,"bodyHtml":"<p><code>eunomia-template</code>：使用 GitHub Actions 编译 eBPF 程序，并将生成的 <code>package.json</code> 发布为 Release 资产。历史上的 <code>ebpm-template</code> 仓库现在会重定向到这里。</p>\n<p>请参考：<a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-template\">https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-template</a></p>\n<h1 id=\"a-template-for-eunomia-bpf-programs\">A template for eunomia-bpf programs</h1>\n<p>This is a template for eunomia-bpf eBPF programs. You can use it as a template, compile it online with <code>GitHub Actions</code>, or build it offline.</p>\n<h3 id=\"compile-and-run-the-ebpf-code-as-simple-as-possible\">Compile and run the eBPF code as simple as possible!</h3>\n<p>Download the pre-compiled <code>ecli</code> binary from here: <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/releases\">eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf</a></p>\n<p>To install, just download and use the <code>ecli</code> binary from here: <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/releases\">eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf</a>:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">wget https://aka.pw/bpf-ecli -O ecli &#x26;&#x26; chmod +x ecli</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"use-this-repo-as-a-github-template-for-online-compilation\">use this repo as a GitHub template for online compilation</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>use this repo as a github template: see <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/creating-a-repository-from-a-template\">creating-a-repository-from-a-template</a></li>\n<li>modify <code>src/template.bpf.c</code>, commit it, and wait for the <code>publish.yml</code> workflow to finish</li>\n<li>download the generated <code>src/package.json</code> asset from the latest release of your fork and run it locally:</li>\n</ol>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ sudo ./ecli run package.json</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"quick-start\">quick start</h2>\n<p>just write some code in the <code>bootstrap.bpf.c</code>, after that, simply run this:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> docker</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -it</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -v</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> /path/to/repo:/src</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ghcr.io/eunomia-bpf/ecc-`</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">uname</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -m</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">`</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">:latest</span><span style=\"color:#768390\"> # use absolute path</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>you will get a <code>package.json</code> in your root dir. Just run:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./ecli</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> package.json</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>The ebpf compiled code can run on different kernel versions(CO-RE). You can just copied the json to another machine.\nsee: <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf\">github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf</a> for the runtime, and <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-cc\">eunomia-bpf/eunomia-cc</a> for our compiler tool chains.</p>\n<h2 id=\"the-code-here\">The code here</h2>\n<p>This is an example of eBPF code. The template currently ships <code>src/template.bpf.c</code> and <code>src/template.h</code>; adjust those files for your own program and let the workflow publish the resulting <code>package.json</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"more-examples\">more examples</h2>\n<p>for more examples, please see: <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/tree/master/examples/bpftools\">eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/tree/master/examples/bpftools</a></p>","tags":[],"headings":[{"id":"compile-and-run-the-ebpf-code-as-simple-as-possible","text":"Compile and run the eBPF code as simple as possible!","depth":3},{"id":"use-this-repo-as-a-github-template-for-online-compilation","text":"use this repo as a GitHub template for online compilation","depth":2},{"id":"quick-start","text":"quick start","depth":2},{"id":"the-code-here","text":"The code here","depth":2},{"id":"more-examples","text":"more examples","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-08T04:58:07.000Z","createdAt":"2023-08-10T12:54:12.000Z","authors":[{"name":"云微","email":"1067852565@qq.com"},{"name":"oluceps","email":"ospp@oluceps.uk"}]},"path":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template/","alternates":{"en":"/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template/","zh":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","description":"![GitHub release (latest by date)](https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/releases) ![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf)","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/"},"previous":{"title":"ecc docker usage","description":"``shell yourprogram.bpf.c yourprogram.h optional, if you want to use ring buffer to export events ``","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage/"},"next":{"title":"eunomia-cc","description":"- A toolchain to simplify writing eBPF programs - Build eBPF programs with Wasm","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","items":[{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/","depth":0},{"title":"Project architecture","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/architecture/","depth":1},{"title":"benchmark","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/benchmark/","depth":1},{"title":"ecc docker usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage/","depth":2},{"title":"github template","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template/","depth":2},{"title":"eunomia-cc","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/","depth":1},{"title":"ecc usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"ecli dockerfile usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/ecli-dockerfile-usage/","depth":2},{"title":"ecli","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/","depth":1},{"title":"ecli server","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/server/","depth":2},{"title":"exporter","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/","depth":1},{"title":"usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"introduction","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/introduction/","depth":1},{"title":"eunomia-bpf 用户手册: 让 eBPF 程序的开发和部署尽可能简单","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/manual/","depth":1},{"title":"在线体验网站","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/online/","depth":1},{"title":"quickstart","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/quickstart/","depth":1},{"title":"build on android aarch64","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/build-android-arm/","depth":2},{"title":"build from source","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/build/","depth":2},{"title":"Install ecli and ecc","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/","depth":1},{"title":"supporting-external-BTF","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/supporting-external-BTF/","depth":1},{"title":"video","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/video/","depth":1}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}